                    ***** WELCOME TO WINPROOF 1.0 *****
             This is the grammar checker you've been waiting for.
                        Installation Instructions:
In DOS, make a new directory for WinProof and switch to it.  Example:
 MKDIR WINPROOF
 CD WINPROOF
Then type the command A:INSTALL if you are installing from drive A: or
B:INSTALL B: if you are installing from drive B:.

To install and run WinProof as an icon , use the program manager "New"
command to create a program item. Place the full pathname of WINPROOF.EXE
in the "command" entry. Click on the WinProof icon to start WinProof.

   To learn how to use PC-Proof read the file WINPROOF.DOC
   If you have problems using the program, read the file HELPME.DOC
   If you are a shareware distributor, read the file VENDOR.DOC

WinProof is being distributed as shareware and requires a $45 registration
fee if you wish to continue using WinProof beyond a 30-day trial period.
Please read the license agreement contained in WINPROOF.DOC. Fill out ORDER.FRM
or CompuServe users can GO SWREG to register. (CompuServe ID 72630,3457)

